testcase.name: two variation percentage rules return the correct variation depending on the candidate()
evaluate a single rule should return true()
chained rules returns false when the parent condition is false()
evaluate a two rules should return true when all evaluations are true()
chained rules returns true when the parent and its children condition are true()
chained rules returns false when its children condition are false()
evaluate a two rules should return true when at least on evaluation is true()
two sibling rules returns true when at least one rule condition is true()
